<a href='http://herbaria4.herb.berkeley.edu/eflora_display.php?tid=322'><h3>View taxon page for Arnica</h3></a><blockquote><h3></h3>
<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 0 ;"><a href="#FC1'">1.</a><a name="FC1."> </a> Pappus 0 <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=80293">.....&nbsp;A. dealbata</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 0 ;"><a href="#FC1.">1'</a><a name="FC1'"> </a> Pappus of 10&ndash;50 fine bristles

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#FC2'">2.</a><a name="FC2."> </a> Heads discoid, some marginal flowers occasionally with &plusmn; expanded corollas

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#FC3'">3.</a><a name="FC3."> </a> Leaves widely &plusmn; sessile

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#FC4'">4.</a><a name="FC4."> </a> Leaf toothed, net-veined abaxially between 3&ndash;5 prominent veins; corolla yellow; fruit hairy, nonglandular <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1152">.....&nbsp;A. venosa</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#FC4.">4'</a><a name="FC4'"> </a> Leaf &plusmn; entire, weakly 3&ndash;5-veined; corolla cream; fruit stalked-glandular <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1153">.....&nbsp;A. viscosa</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#FC3.">3'</a><a name="FC3'"> </a> Proximal and middle leaves narrowed to a &plusmn; widely winged petiole (except <I>Arnica discoidea</I>, proximal leaves &plusmn; narrowly wing-petioled)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#FC5'">5.</a><a name="FC5."> </a> Phyllaries linear to lanceolate; young heads generally nodding; pappus brown-yellow, &plusmn; plumose <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1144">.....&nbsp;A. parryi</a> (2)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#FC5.">5'</a><a name="FC5'"> </a> Phyllaries narrowly lanceolate to lance-ovate; young heads erect; pappus white, generally short-barbed

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#FC6'">6.</a><a name="FC6."> </a> Most proximal leaf blades lanceolate to ovate or &plusmn; cordate; petiole narrow, &plusmn; narrowly winged; fruit hairy and stalked-glandular <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1123">.....&nbsp;A. discoidea</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#FC6.">6'</a><a name="FC6'"> </a> Most proximal leaf blades &plusmn; oblanceolate; petiole &plusmn; widely winged; fruit sparsely stalked-glandular, generally otherwise glabrous <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1149">.....&nbsp;A. spathulata</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#FC2.">2'</a><a name="FC2'"> </a> Heads radiate

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#FC7'">7.</a><a name="FC7."> </a> Cauline leaves generally 5&ndash;12 pairs, &plusmn; equal or gradually reduced distally on stem; heads 3&ndash;20

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#FC8'">8.</a><a name="FC8."> </a> Phyllaries generally &plusmn; obtuse, adaxial face of tip generally hair-tufted; tube of disk corolla generally 3&ndash;4.5 mm <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1115">.....&nbsp;A. chamissonis</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#FC8.">8'</a><a name="FC8'"> </a> Phyllaries &plusmn; acute, tip &plusmn; no more hairy than body; tube of disk corolla generally 2&ndash;3 mm

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#FC9'">9.</a><a name="FC9."> </a> Stems 1&ndash;few from short rhizome or caudex; leaves &plusmn; toothed <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=82177">.....&nbsp;A. lanceolata subsp. prima</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#FC9.">9'</a><a name="FC9'"> </a> Stems clustered on short caudex-like rhizome; leaves &plusmn; entire <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1139">.....&nbsp;A. longifolia</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#FC7.">7'</a><a name="FC7'"> </a> Cauline leaves generally 2&ndash;4(6) pairs, often strongly reduced distally on stem; heads generally &lt; 5(15)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#FC10'">10.</a><a name="FC10."> </a> Pappus (yellow-)brown, bristles &plusmn; plumose &mdash; rhizome short, freely rooting

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#FC11'">11.</a><a name="FC11."> </a> Rays &lt; 15 mm; proximal herbage &plusmn; long-spreading-hairy; young heads generally nodding <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1144">.....&nbsp;A. parryi</a> (2)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#FC11.">11'</a><a name="FC11'"> </a> Rays generally 15&ndash;25 mm; proximal herbage becoming glabrous to hairy or glandular; young heads erect

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#FC12'">12.</a><a name="FC12."> </a> Heads spreading-bell-shaped to hemispheric; cauline leaves variable, &plusmn; sessile, most proximal generally largest <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1141">.....&nbsp;A. mollis</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#FC12.">12'</a><a name="FC12'"> </a> Heads &plusmn; narrowly obconic; cauline leaf blades elliptic to widely deltate, at least some petioled, middle generally largest <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=82179">.....&nbsp;A. ovata</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#FC10.">10'</a><a name="FC10'"> </a> Pappus &plusmn; white to straw-colored, bristles short-barbed, if bristles &plusmn; plumose, rhizome long

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#FC13'">13.</a><a name="FC13."> </a> Leaf blade narrow, length &plusmn; 3&ndash;6+ &times; width; basal leaves generally densely clustered; rays yellow-orange

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#FC14'">14.</a><a name="FC14."> </a> Proximal axils brown-woolly-tufted; disk corollas spreading-hairy, stalked-glandular <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1130">.....&nbsp;A. fulgens</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#FC14.">14'</a><a name="FC14'"> </a> Proximal axils glabrous or sparsely white-hairy; disk corollas stalked-glandular only <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1148">.....&nbsp;A. sororia</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#FC13.">13'</a><a name="FC13'"> </a> Leaf blade generally &plusmn; wide, length generally &lt; 2.5 &times; width; basal leaves sometimes persistent, not densely clustered; rays yellow

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#FC15'">15.</a><a name="FC15."> </a> Cauline leaves at least at mid-stem sessile (&plusmn; sessile) <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1133">.....&nbsp;A. latifolia</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#FC15.">15'</a><a name="FC15'"> </a> Cauline leaves at least at mid-stem petioled (petiole &plusmn; wide)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 42 ;"><a href="#FC16'">16.</a><a name="FC16."> </a> Leaves &plusmn; thick, often fleshy and &plusmn; red; heads 1(4), often nodding in bud; serpentine soils <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1113">.....&nbsp;A. cernua</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 42 ;"><a href="#FC16.">16'</a><a name="FC16'"> </a> Leaves &plusmn; thin, neither fleshy nor &plusmn; red; heads 1&ndash;5, not nodding in bud; not on serpentine

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 49 ;"><a href="#FC17'">17.</a><a name="FC17."> </a> Proximal leaves generally toothed, &plusmn; strongly cordate (except stunted alpine plants); pappus short-barbed <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1118">.....&nbsp;A. cordifolia</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 49 ;"><a href="#FC17.">17'</a><a name="FC17'"> </a> Proximal leaves &plusmn; entire, base rounded (&plusmn; cordate); pappus short-barbed to &plusmn; plumose <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1142">.....&nbsp;A. nevadensis</a></blockquote><P>
